               <msContents>
                  <summary>A volume of the <title>Tuḥfat al-Muʼminīn</title> (Gift of the Believers)
                     a medical anthology composed by Muḥammad Muʼmin Ḥusaynī (d. 1698) and dedicated
                     to the Safavid ruler dedicated to Safavid ruler <persName role="dte"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/232859004" key="person_232859004">S̲h̲āh Sulaymān
                        I (b. 1648 r. 1666–1694)</persName>, in his effort to correct innaccuracies
                     that he found in the prevailing pharmacopoeia at the time, <title
                        key="work_1161">Ik̲h̲tiyārāt-i Badīʿī</title>. In doing so, he primarily
                     relied upon several other medical works to formulate his own. He divides the
                     work into two major divisions: the first entitled <title>Tashkhīṣ</title>
                     consists of five chapters, and the second part, <title>Dastūrāt</title>,
                     contains three further subdivisions. An unidentified scribe completed this
                     volume in </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_569-item1">
                     <author key="person_36318254" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/36318254/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ḥusaynī, Muḥammad Muʼmin,
                           d. 1698</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Tunukābunī, Muḥammad
                           Muʼmin</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">حسينی، محمد مؤمن بن مير محمد زمان <addName
                              xml:lang="ar" type="nisbah">تنكابنی ديلمی</addName>
                        </persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="dte" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/232859004" key="person_232859004">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">S̲h̲āh Sulaymān I, b. 1648 r.
                           1666–1694</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">شاه سلیمان اول</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1072">Tuḥfat al-muʼminīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_1072">تحفة المؤمنين</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1072">Tuḥfat al-mu’minīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_1072">تحفة المؤمنین</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmala"><locus from="3b" to="3b"> برگ ۳پ (folio
                           3b):</locus> سبحانک اللهم یا قدوس و یا طبیب النفوس اتمم لنا انوار معرفتک
                        و ارزقنا ... </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="508a" to="508a"> برگ ۵۰۸ر (folio 508a):</locus> ...از خردن آن
                        طیور هیوش(؟) کردند چون دبق را با عسل دو و ساب طبخ بلنیع داده مانند رلیمان
                        براستجار و غیر آن گذارند طیوری که نران نشبند(؟) بست کردند و الله تعالی اعلم
                        بخواص الا دویه</explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="508a" to="508a"> برگ ۵۰۸ر (folio 508a):</locus> تم تم تمامشد
                        معالجات و دستورات المعطرات، تشخیصات تحفة المومنین بعون الله تعالی و حسن
                        توفیق را نیاز(؟) سنه ۱۱۹۹</colophon>
                     <colophon>Completed <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" from="1784" to="1785">1199
                           AH (1784–1785 CE)</date>.</colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>For two other copies of this work held in the Rylands, see <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7274">77</ref> and
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26566"
                              ><idno>Persian MS 966</idno></ref>.</note>
                  </msItem>

               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>Textblock of medium-weight, straight and cross-grained, externally
                           sized and polished, butter-coloured <material>paper</material> probably
                           handmade in the <placeName cert="high"
                              ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208" key="place_7000208"
                              >Indian subcontinent</placeName> with ~9 laid lines per cm and no
                           discernible chain lines.</support>
                        <extent>
                           <measure unit="folio" quantity="511">511 folios, 2 flyleaves (ff. i + 511
                              + i)</measure>. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>260</height>
                              <width>150</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>202</height>
                              <width>102</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>

                        <foliation xml:id="original">Incomplete inked Hindu-Arabic numerals added to
                           the upper-left corners of the a sides on the first two hundred folios
                           only.</foliation>
                        <foliation xml:id="modern">Modern pencilled Arabic numerals added to the
                           upper-left corners of the a sides, inclusive of the original endpapers,
                           referenced for this record</foliation>

                        <collation> Undetermined. <catchwords>Catchwords throughout most of the
                              lower-left corners of the b sides.</catchwords></collation>
                        <condition>In fair condition, with moderate water and insect damage and
                           historical repairs throughout.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="23" n="mistara"> Written in 1 column with 23
                           lines per page. Ruled with a <hi rend="italic">misṭarah</hi> hand
                           guide.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" script="nasta_liq" medium="ink"> Written in clear
                           <material>black</material> nasta‘līq with <material>red</material>
                        subheaders and markings. </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="marginal"><lb/><label>Ruling:</label> Margins ruled in
                           <material>yellow</material> outlined with thin internal single red and
                        external double black lines, surrounded by another comparatively thick dark
                        blue single line, the last repeated again on the outer margins.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <lb/>
