                     <label>Bookplates:</label>
                     <locus from="Inner_back_cover" to="Inner_back_cover">Left pastedown</locus>: <q
                        xml:lang="en">Bibliotheca Lindesiana</q> with pencilled shelfmark <q
                        xml:lang="en">1/F</q>, and <q xml:lang="en"><hi rend="strikethrough"
                           >Hamilton</hi> MSS No. <hi rend="strikethrough">486</hi></q>, with the
                     name and number crossed out and <q xml:lang="en">Persian</q> and <q
                        xml:lang="en">569</q> written aside. </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1775" notAfter="1838">
                        <p>Possibly originally bound in <placeName
                              ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001502" key="place_7001502"
                              >Awadh</placeName>, due to the similarity of the combed patterned
                           bindings closely comparing with those acquired there by Antoine Polier
                           and others. </p>
                        <decoNote type="binding">Likely unsupported sewing, subsequently resewn at
                           five stations. Neither evidence of recent trimming nor endbands. The
                           edges of the pasteboards partially hemmed in brown goatskin
                              <material>leather</material> faced with vivid combed marbled paper,
                           with the spine and part of the head edge later replaced. Internal
                           pastedowns of the same marbled paper as used on the exterior, with hinges
                           of later British-made 'Spanish' wave-patterned marbled paper, and a later
                           cream-coloured machine-made European mould-made flyleaves, added when
                           rebacked.</decoNote>
                        <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                              <height>262</height>
                              <width>157</width>
                              <depth>65</depth>
                           </dimensions></p>
                        <condition>Binding in fair but stable condition.</condition>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
